The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, May 9: Manufacturing growth is likely to slow down to 11 per cent during April-June compared with an estimated 15 per cent expansion in the previous quarter because of rising raw material prices, a Ficci survey said. Chemical and allied products, which have a significant share in the overall manufacturing sector, are likely to pull down growth in the first quarter of the current fiscal.                             
	 Mumbai, May 9: ICICI Prudential Life Insurance has posted its maiden profit of Rs 258 crore in 2009-10. Our key focus for 2010 was profitability. We also tried to avoid infusing capital. We launched an array of low-charge products that gave us a very good top-line revenue and also cut costs, CEO and managing director V. Vaidyanathan said.                             
	 New Delhi, May 9: HDFC Bank is set to venture into silver bar trade from next week. We will start selling silver bars from our branches from the auspicious day of Akshaya Tritiya (May 16), Seshan Ramakrishnan, group head (retail liabilities products), said.                             
	 New Delhi, May 9: Four state-run banks  Vijaya Bank, the Central Bank of India, Uco Bank and the United Bank of India  are likely to get Rs 1,500 crore as part of their recapitalisation package soon, according to sources.                            
	 New Delhi, May 9: Government auditor CAG has pulled up the department of telecommunications for not utilising funds of over Rs 18,000 crore collected for promoting rural telephony and giving a false picture about the unused sums.                            
	 New Delhi, May 9: The new wholesale price-based inflation basket will have 676 products, including LCD televisions, mobile phones and packaged drinking water. The list is likely to be rolled out in June or July.                            
	 Calcutta, May 9: KBC Agro Products, an India-Bangladesh joint venture having Phoenix Overseas, Kalyani Solvex, Bansal Oil and Chowdhury Enterprise as partners, has set up a solvent extraction plant in Dhaka to make rice bran oil.                                                                                                                          
